HEADWORD: monocystic
<hw>mon`o*cys"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Mono-</er>, and <er>Cyst</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Of or
pertaining to a division (<fam>Monocystidea</fam>) of the protozoan
order <ord>Gregarinida</ord>, in which the body consists of one
sac.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

